The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 November is 7,724 (894 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 November, there were 934 new confirmed cases (108.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 November, there were 836 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 12% ( 98 extra cases).
